<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 06 at 4:00AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Haskell, south central McIntosh, northwestern Latimer and
northeastern Pittsburg Counties through 445 AM CDT...
At 400 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Crowder, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Wilburton...                      Stigler...
Quinton...                        Crowder...
Whitefield...                     Kinta...
Canadian...                       Blocker...
Robbers Cave State Park...        Arrowhead State Park...
Enterprise...                     Lequire...
Panola...                         Featherston...
Lewisville...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
